# UI UX Lead Design Intelligence

**This rule enforces the repo's UI UX Lead workflow for all UI, frontend, layout, design system, styling, and UX tasks.**

## Default Entry Point

For any substantial UI/UX task, start here first:

```
plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/ui-ux-lead/SKILL.md
```

Related reusable agent prompt:

```
plugins/portfolio-tools/agents/ui-ux-lead.md
```

The UI UX Lead workflow is the repo-standard orchestration layer. It requires the agent to consult `ui-ux-pro-max` together with the project design skills instead of treating design work as isolated styling.

## Skill Location

The design intelligence modules live at:

```
plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/ui-ux-lead/
ai-skills/ui-ux-pro-max/
```

Key paths:
- **UI UX Lead skill**: `plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/ui-ux-lead/SKILL.md`
- **UI UX Lead agent**: `plugins/portfolio-tools/agents/ui-ux-lead.md`
- **SKILL.md**: `ai-skills/ui-ux-pro-max/.claude/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md`
- **Search script**: `ai-skills/ui-ux-pro-max/.claude/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py`
- **Design datasets**: `ai-skills/ui-ux-pro-max/.claude/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/data/`

## Mandatory Consultation

When a task involves any of the following, you **must** invoke the UI UX Lead workflow before generating code:

| Task Type | Examples |
|-----------|----------|
| Landing pages | Hero sections, conversion flows, CTAs |
| Dashboards | Data visualization, admin panels, analytics |
| Product UI | SaaS interfaces, e-commerce, app screens |
| Component libraries | Buttons, cards, modals, forms, tables |
| Design systems | Colors, typography, spacing, tokens |
| Frontend architecture | Layout patterns, responsive behavior, animations |

## Global Header/Footer Constraint

The shared `components/Header.tsx` and `components/Footer.tsx` always remain the public site chrome. If a supplied HTML landing page, mockup, or reference includes its own header, nav, language switcher, footer, or footer CTA, ignore that chrome and adapt only the body/page content between the global Header and Footer. Do not replace, duplicate, hide, or visually override the universal Header/Footer unless the user explicitly asks to change the global components themselves.

## Required Process

1. **Read the UI UX Lead skill** – Parse `plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/ui-ux-lead/SKILL.md`.

2. **Read UI-UX Pro Max** – Parse `ai-skills/ui-ux-pro-max/.claude/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md`.

3. **Generate design system** (for new pages/projects) – Run the search script with `--design-system`:
   ```bash
   python3 ai-skills/ui-ux-pro-max/.claude/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product_type> <industry> <keywords>" --design-system -p "Project Name"
   ```

4. **Domain-specific search** (as needed) – For style, color, typography, or UX details:
   ```bash
   python3 ai-skills/ui-ux-pro-max/.claude/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<keyword>" --domain <style|color|typography|ux|landing|chart>
   ```

5. **Read project design skills** – At minimum, consult:
   - `plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/design-system/SKILL.md`
   - `plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/visual-hierarchy/SKILL.md`

6. **Apply guidance** – Use the combined guidance to generate structured frontend code with coherent spacing, hierarchy, copy density, and interaction design.

## Integration with Project Skills

This skill **complements** (does not replace) the project's existing skills:
- `design-system/SKILL.md` – Design tokens and CSS variables
- `visual-hierarchy/SKILL.md` – Layout and decluttering

For UI tasks: invoke `ui-ux-lead`, then consult the required project skills and UI-UX Pro Max through that workflow.

## Pre-Delivery Checklist (from skill)

- [ ] No emojis as icons (use SVG: Heroicons/Lucide)
- [ ] `cursor-pointer` on all clickable elements
- [ ] Hover states with smooth transitions (150–300ms)
- [ ] Light mode: text contrast 4.5:1 minimum
- [ ] Focus states visible for keyboard nav
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected
- [ ] Responsive: 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px
